commits.message:
rdir: implement meta2/count request

This new request counts the number of records for a specific meta2
database. Also fix a bunch of memory leaks.
rdir: include the list of volumes in /status responses
rdir: add the number of databases per meta2 service in /status
rawx: refactor to handle gracefull restart (OBSTO-1855)
tests: make rdir tests clean the crap they produce

tests: define identifiable names for test objects

Many tests do not clean what they create. Giving clear names will help
understand which tests must be improved so they don't influence other
tests.
xcute: allow to exclude some rawx services automatically
CI: try to get xcute code coverage

sharding: Use urgent mode when cleaning timeout

Cleaning the shard in the customer path should have
as little impact as possible.
But if the customer makes too many requests on its shard
to the point of preventing the cleanup, using urgent mode
(temporarily) prevents the cleanup from failing.

meta2: leave elections cleanly before shutting down

On SIGTERM signal, leave elections cleanly before shutting down.
On SIGINT signal, do a fast shutdown, just leave elections locally.

Also, add an option to "balance masters" preventing a service which just
left an election to rejoin it immediatly after.
meta2: improve the autoconf of the maximum number of open databases
meta2: verify content and chunks are read from db
rawx: refactor to handle gracefull restart (OBSTO-1855)
meta2: verify content and chunks are read from db
Make mover choose local placement in priority
Refactor: introduce get_file_hash method
meta2: verify content and chunks are read from db

sharding: Avoid vacuum operations on client-accessible databases

By default, VACUUM is disabled because there is "auto_vacuum" which
can do it afterwards (taking care not to disturb the client too much).

sharding: Vacuum as soon as a cleaning request is successful

If VACUUM is requested, it should be triggered, after attempting
to clean the shard, as soon as a cleaning request is successful.
CI: Test the VACUUM operations during the sharding
